  "response": "Some movies from around the world that include nude scenes (non-pornographic) span various genres, cultures, and artistic intentions. Here\u2019s a list of notable examples:\n\n---\n\n### **Hollywood and English-Language Films**\n1. **Blue is the Warmest Color** (2013) - France  \n   A critically acclaimed French film with intimate and explicit scenes.\n\n2. **The Wolf of Wall Street** (2013) - USA  \n   Includes nudity in party and decadence scenes.\n\n3. **American Beauty** (1999) - USA  \n   Features nudity in a symbolic and artistic context.\n\n4. **Eyes Wide Shut** (1999) - USA/UK  \n   Directed by Stanley Kubrick, it explores themes of sexuality and includes explicit scenes.\n\n5. **Shame** (2011) - UK/USA  \n   A drama about addiction and intimacy with explicit content.\n\n---\n\n### **European Films**\n6. **Love** (2015) - France  \n   A French film with explicit and emotional scenes.\n\n7. **9 Songs** (2004) - UK  \n   Known for its explicit sexual content intertwined with music.\n\n8. **Antichrist** (2009) - Denmark  \n   A controversial Lars von Trier film with explicit and disturbing scenes.\n\n9. **The Piano Teacher** (2001) - Austria/France  \n   A psychological drama with sexual and nude scenes.\n\n10. **Nymphomaniac** (2013) - Denmark/France  \n    Lars von Trier\u2019s two-part film exploring sexuality.\n\n---\n\n### **Asian Films**\n11. **In the Mood for Love** (2000) - Hong Kong  \n    While not explicit, it has sensually charged scenes.\n\n12. **The Handmaiden** (2016) - South Korea  \n    A beautifully crafted film with intimate and sensual scenes.\n\n13. **Lust, Caution** (2007) - Taiwan/China  \n    Directed by Ang Lee, it includes explicit scenes.\n\n14. **Taboo** (1999) - Japan  \n    A film exploring sexuality in feudal Japan.\n\n---\n\n### **Other International Films**\n15. **Y Tu Mam\u00e1 Tambi\u00e9n** (2001) - Mexico  \n    A coming-of-age road trip film with nude scenes.\n\n16. **Romance** (1999) - France  \n    A French film with explicit sexual content.\n\n17. **The Apartment** (1996) - Argentina  \n    A romantic drama with intimate scenes.\n\n---\n\nThese films often use nudity to explore themes of intimacy, vulnerability, or societal norms, rather than for titillation. Viewer discretion is advised.",
